What is this program?
=====================

Well to be precise, it is a text file ENCRYPTOR/DECRYPTOR.
It allows you to encode any text files in a code of your choice.

It allows you to decode text files that a friend/collegue has sent to 
you via e-mail, so that only you and he/she will know the contents.

It also allows you to break coded messages that you may have intercepted.

It is, in essence, a coder/decoder...a help at both encoding and decoding 
messages.

Codes and Ciphers:
==================

There are two types of secret code.

1) A simple LETTER SUBSITUTION code  =  A Cipher
2) A word substitution/movement  =  A Code 



The differences between a Code and a Cipher:
============================================

A code is basically scrambling up a message, perhaps replacing real
words with made up words...

IE: the word "HELLO" could become "KRATCHNEE".

There is no pattern involved in the transfer, the second CODE WORD can be
absolutely anything.

To use a CODE between yourself and a collegue, each participating member
of your group must have a file with the words listed:

EXAMPLE:


                              MY CODEBOOK 
                              ===========

 A          = Womble
 Am         = Fridgelock
 Hello      = Crazyman
 I          = Poopascoop
 Programmer = Wobbajob
 Signed     = YummyPoo
 Steve      = BigNastyDood 

To contruct a sentence you would just match the words with their equal.

EG: the sentence "Hello, I am a programmer - Signed: Steve"
    would become:

 "Crazyman, Poopascoop Fridgelock Womble Wobbajob - YummyPoo: BigNastyDood"

There we have a simple code. All you would need to do is make CODE WORDS
for each real word that you think you would need to use and give a copy
of your code dictionary (list of words) to the person who would receive
the coded message.

A Code can also have one word that stands for several words.

EG: "Help, I am being bored to death by a programmer" could be translated
    into:
   
    "Erk joop nip nop scallywag"   

I have made up those on the spot here, so they have no real meaning..
The code dictionary could have the words listed as:

  Help                 = Erk
  I am                 = joop
  being bored to death = nip 
  by a                 = nop
  programmer           = scallywag

CIPHERS:
========

If a code is one or more words replaced by one other word, then a cipher
must be different.

A cipher is a completely new alphabet constructed for the sole purpose
of confusing an enemy.

An example cipher might be:

a = 1
b = 2
c = 3
d = 4
e = 5

etc.

A message could then be written using the new alphabet.

The cipher is what Gui-coder can decrypt best. If you have a coded message
that you think has letters substituted then you could make up several 
alphabets and run the message through the coder (set on decode) to see if
the result looks like a proper message.

Gui-Coder will not try running different letters against each other to find
a decent result.
 
(though maybe in the future I will make a version that can do this)

It will still rely on you to think up the alphabet...All coder does
is substitute the cipher alphabet for the real one (and vice versa).


