How to install this product:

Copy the drawer Gui-Coder to somewhere on your hard drive.

Add an assign of CODER: to the path where Coder is.
Add the assign to your user-startup (located in s:)

That's it!!

@EndNode

@Node "Usage"
@Next "Crypt"
@Prev "Insta"
@Toc "Main"

How to use this great product:

On the main window you will see 5 large sections:

The first section labelled @{b}Encryption details@{ub} contains 4 buttons with labels:
    This labels are as follows:
     
       ENCIPHER LETTERS USING SELECTED CODE = This encrypts/decrypts text
                                              using a code selected else
                                              where on the page.
   
       CONVERT LETTERS TO BINARY CODE = This changes every letter in the 
                                        text to (or from) its binary code.
 
       CONVERT LETTERS TO THEIR ASCII HEX-CODE = This changes every letter
                                                 in the text to (or from)
                                                 its ascii hexidecimal code.

       ENCODE THE TEXT BY WRITING IT BACKWARDS = Writes each line of text 
                                                 reversed to the way it was.

The second section labelled @{b}OPTIONS@{ub} contains 3 select boxes:
   Their labels are as follows:
           
       ENCODE/DECODE? = When selected coder will encode files, when blank
                        coder will decode files.
 
       DELETE INPUT FILE = When selected coder will delete the original text
                           that has been selected for encoding/decoding.

       REMOVE SPACES FROM TEXT = When selected coder will remove all spaces 
                                 from the text that has been selected for coding
                                 or decoding.

The third section labelled @{b}File Selection@{b} contains 2 text entry points
and several buttons.

The text entry points are labelled @{b}Input File@{ub} and @{b}Output File@{ub}.

Input file is the file you wish to be coded/encoded. To specify which file this is
you can do either:

  A) specify it in the text entry box or 
  B) select it with the file selection button (Piece of paper with corner folded) 

Output file is the result coded/encoded file. To specify which file this is
you can do either:

  A) specify it in the text entry box or 
  B) select it with the file selection button (Piece of paper with corner folded) 

The buttons with the arrows pointing downwards:     |
                                                   \|/
                                                   ~~~
are the buttons which when pressed will edit the file specified in the 
text entry box using the editor which is specified further down the menu.

The next section labelled @{b}Code Selection@{ub} is where you specify which
cipher you wish to use when coding/decoding using the 
"ENCIPHER LETTERS USING SELECTED CODE" function.
To choose the code simply fill in the text entry box or select it with the
file selection button. You can edit the code using the EDIT button (with the arrow).

The second to last section labelled @{b}Editor Options@{ub} is where you specify which
editor you wish to use when editing/viewing the Input/Output/Code files.
The added "Options" text entry is for programs such as ED who require the option
"%s" to stop them from blocking the Coder program.

The final section which is unlabelled has 2 buttons:

"START" which activates the encoding/decoding.
 
         and

"EXIT" which leaves Gui-Coder without encoding/decoding


MAKING CIPHERS:
===============

You can make your own codes/ciphers by creating a normal text file with your
favourite editor...

THEN..

Write your cipher/code out in full with the alphabet below it...
The top line should all be in uppercase.
The bottom line should all be in lower case

EG:

QWERTYUIOPASDFGHJKLZXCVBNM0987654321
qwertyuiopasdfghjklzxcvbnm0987654321

ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVQXYZ1234567890

This code was made using the Keyboard...If you look you will notice the
alphabet corresponds with the keys on the keyboard starting from the left
at the top and moving along to the right...then progressively moving DOWN
the keyboard.

Just save your code in the drawer CODER:CODES as "{NAME OF CODE}.code"

@EndNode

